@startuml Exploding Kittens Class Diagram

' ── PlantUML Syntax Guide ─────────────────────────────────
'
' ── Visibility Modifiers (inside classes) ────────────────
' +  → public   (accessible by everyone)
' -  → private  (accessible only within the class)
' #  → protected (accessible within class and subclasses)
'
' ── Relationships ─────────────────────────────────────────
' ..>   → dependency: "uses" (weakest relationship)
'          e.g. A ..> B means A uses B somewhere
'
' -->   → association: "has a reference to"
'          e.g. GameController --> GameState means
'          GameController holds a reference to GameState
'
' ..|>  → realization/implementation: "implements an interface"
'          e.g. GameView ..|> IGameDisplay means
'          GameView implements IGameDisplay
'
' --|>  → inheritance: "extends a class"
'          e.g. Dog --|> Animal means Dog extends Animal
'
' *--   → composition: "owns it, it cannot exist without me"
'          e.g. GameState "1" *-- "1" Deck means
'          Deck is destroyed when GameState is destroyed
'
' o--   → aggregation: "has it, but it can exist without me"
'          e.g. GameState "1" o-- "*" Card : discardPile means
'          Cards exist independently of GameState
'
' ── Multiplicity (the numbers on relationships) ──────────
' "1"  → exactly one
' "*"  → zero or more
' "1..*" → one or more
'          e.g. GameState "1" *-- "*" Player means
'          one GameState owns zero or more Players
'

' ── Enums ────────────────────────────────────────────────
enum CardType {
  EXPLODING_KITTEN
  DEFUSE
  SKIP
  ATTACK
  SHUFFLE
  SEE_THE_FUTURE
  FAVOR
  NOPE
  CAT_CARD
}

enum GameStatus {
  ACTIVE
  ENDED
}

' ── Card Action Strategy ──────────────────────────────────
interface CardAction {
  + execute(gameState: GameState): void
}

class SkipAction implements CardAction
class AttackAction implements CardAction
class ShuffleAction implements CardAction
class SeeTheFutureAction implements CardAction
class NopeAction implements CardAction
class DefuseAction implements CardAction

class PlayerInteractionHelper {
  + stealRandomCard(from: Player, to: Player): void
  + stealNamedCard(from: Player, to: Player, type: CardType): void
}

class FavorAction {
  - helper: PlayerInteractionHelper
  + execute(gameState: GameState): void
}

class TwoCatAction {
  - helper: PlayerInteractionHelper
  + execute(gameState: GameState): void
}

class ThreeCatAction {
  - helper: PlayerInteractionHelper
  + execute(gameState: GameState): void
}

FavorAction    ..|> CardAction
TwoCatAction   ..|> CardAction
ThreeCatAction ..|> CardAction

class ComboValidator {
  + isValid(cards: List<Card>): boolean
  + resolveAction(cards: List<Card>): CardAction
}

' ── Model ────────────────────────────────────────────────
class Card {
  - type: CardType
  - name: String
  - action: CardAction
  + isType(type: CardType): boolean
  + execute(gameState: GameState): void
}

class Player {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - hand: List<Card>
  - peekCards: List<Card>
  + addCard(card: Card): void
  + removeCard(card: Card): void
  + hasCard(type: CardType): boolean
  + getCardOfType(type: CardType): Card
  + storePeek(cards: List<Card>): void
  + clearPeek(): void
}

class Deck {
  - cards: List<Card>
  + shuffle(): void
  + drawTop(): Card
  + insertAt(card: Card, index: int): void
  + size(): int
  + isEmpty(): boolean
}

class DeckFactory {
  + buildDeck(numPlayers: int): Deck
}

class TurnState {
  - turnsToTake: int
  - skipDraw: boolean
  - isAttacking: boolean
  - pendingAction: Card
  - nopeCount: int
  + enableSkipDraw(): void
  + startAttack(turns: int): void
  + setPendingAction(card: Card): void
  + clearPendingAction(): void
  + incrementNopeCount(): void
  + decrementTurns(): void
  + shouldSkipDraw(): boolean
  + isAttacking(): boolean
  + nopeCount(): int
  + turnsRemaining(): int
  + reset(): void
}

class GameState {
  - status: GameStatus
  - activePlayers: Queue<Player>
  - eliminatedPlayers: List<Player>
  - deck: Deck
  - discardPile: List<Card>
  - turnState: TurnState
  + isActive(): boolean
  + endGame(): void
  + getCurrentPlayer(): Player
  + advancePlayer(): void
  + eliminateCurrentPlayer(): void
  + activePlayerCount(): int
  + drawFromDeck(): Card
  + isDeckEmpty(): boolean
  + insertIntoDeck(card: Card, index: int): void
  + shuffleDeck(): void
  + discardCard(card: Card): void
  + addCardToCurrentPlayer(card: Card): void
  + removeCardFromCurrentPlayer(card: Card): void
  + currentPlayerHasCard(type: CardType): boolean
  + turnState(): TurnState
}

' ── View ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
interface IGameDisplay {
  + showGameState(gameState: GameState): void
  + showPlayerHand(player: Player): void
  + showMessage(message: String): void
  + showWinner(player: Player): void
}

interface IPlayerInput {
  + promptCardSelection(player: Player): List<Card>
  + promptNumPlayers(): int
  + promptNope(players: List<Player>): boolean
}

class GameView {
  + showGameState(gameState: GameState): void
  + showPlayerHand(player: Player): void
  + showMessage(message: String): void
  + showWinner(player: Player): void
  + promptCardSelection(player: Player): List<Card>
  + promptNumPlayers(): int
}

GameView ..|> IGameDisplay
GameView ..|> IPlayerInput

' ── Controller ───────────────────────────────────────────
class GameController {
  - gameState: GameState
  - display: IGameDisplay
  - input: IPlayerInput
  - deckFactory: DeckFactory
  - comboValidator: ComboValidator
  + startGame(): void
  + playATurn(): void
  + playCard(cards: List<Card>): void
  + drawCard(): void
  + endGame(): void
}

' ── Relationships ─────────────────────────────────────────
Card --> CardType
Card --> CardAction

GameState --> GameStatus
GameState "1" *-- "1"   Deck      : deck
GameState "1" *-- "*"   Player    : activePlayers
GameState "1" o-- "*"   Player    : eliminatedPlayers
GameState "1" *-- "1"   TurnState : turnState
GameState "1" o-- "*"   Card      : discardPile

Player "1" o-- "*" Card : hand
Deck   "1" *-- "*" Card : cards

FavorAction    *-- PlayerInteractionHelper
TwoCatAction   *-- PlayerInteractionHelper
ThreeCatAction *-- PlayerInteractionHelper

GameController --> GameState
GameController --> IGameDisplay
GameController --> IPlayerInput
GameController --> DeckFactory
GameController --> ComboValidator

ComboValidator --> CardAction

DeckFactory --> Deck

' ── Sticky Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────
note top of IGameDisplay
  Output only, shows things on screen
  showGameState: shows the overall current state to everyone (e.g. whose turn it is, what's in the discard pile)
  showMessage: declares what action was taken, e.g. "Player 1 played attack card"
  showWinner: declares the winner at the end of each game
  showPlayerHand: shows the player's card to the player (each player only sees their own cards, but shouldn't be able
  to see anyone else's)
end note

note top of IPlayerInput
  Input from the user
  promptCardSelection: asks the player which cards they want to play when it's their turn
  promptNumPlayers: asks at the start how many players are playing
  promptNope: asks players if they want to nope at each turn
end note

note top of CardAction
  Strategy Pattern: defines a family of algorithms, encapsulate each into a separate class, making them interchangeable
  at runtime
  Why use Strategy Pattern? Adheres to Open/Close Principle, reduced repetitive if statements
  *Note: actions that are not FavorAction, TwoCatAction, ThreeCatAction did not include execute because there's nothing
  extra to show, but they would fulfill the execute
  Why is it an interface? There are many implementations of what executing a card means for each card.
end note

note top of PlayerInteractionHelper
  Favor Card: stealRandomCard
  Two Cat Card: stealRandomCard
  Three Cat Card: stealNamedCard
  Is a class and not an interface because the stealing logic is the same, no matter what card
  Favors composition over inheritance (helper is PlayerInteractionHelper), greater flexibility
  Uses Delegation: one object passes work to another instead of doing it itself through PlayerInteractionHelper
end note

note top of ComboValidator
  isValid: validates a list of cards to ensure they are valid
  Valid Combination:
  *Any single card action (Skip, Attack, Shuffle, etc.)
  *2 of the same cat card (TwoCatAction)
  *3 of th same cat card (ThreeCatAction)
  Invalid Combination:
  *Mixed cat cards (one Taco Cat + one Beard Cat, they have to match)
  *An action card paired with anything (Skip + cat card makes no sense)
  *Playing Defuse voluntarily from hand (it only triggers on drawing an Exploding Kitten)
  *Playing an Exploding Kitten from hand
  resolveAction: chooses what action to take based on what list of cards the player gives
end note

note top of GameState
  GameState represents the entire game's memory, e.g. who is alive, what's in the deck, discardPile
end note

note top of TurnState
  TurnState is a temporary snapshot of what's happening
  skipDraw: whether the player can skip their draw (e.g. play attack or skip)
  pendingAction: what card is pending a nope window
end note

note top of DeckFactory
  Use factory design pattern to minimize complex logic of GameController
end note

note top of GameView
  Why use 2 interfaces?
  Separation of concerns, follows Interface Segregation since display vs input have different responsibilities
  Since we want to start with a terminal game and get the functionality working first, we can just write a new class
  and in GameController we'd only swap one line, so GameController doesn't have to change. This follows Open/Close
end note

@enduml